On Sat, Feb 10, 2024 at 06:48:03PM +0100, Karsten Hilbert wrote:
> Dear list members,
>
> Debian packaging CI is sending me this:
>
> > gnumed-client 1.8.18+dfsg-1 is marked for autoremoval from testing on 2024-03-15
> >
> > It (build-)depends on packages with these RC bugs:
> > 1062249: libchipcard: NMU diff for 64-bit time_t transition
> >  https://bugs.debian.org/1062249
> > 1062362: libgwenhywfar: NMU diff for 64-bit time_t transition
> >  https://bugs.debian.org/1062362
>
> but according to
>
> 	https://packages.debian.org/source/sid/gnumed-client
>
> the source packages does not build-depend on either and
> according to
>
> 	https://packages.debian.org/source/gnumed-client
>
> it only has a *Suggest* on libchipcard-tools.
>
> So, is the above irrelevant because libchipcard-tools will
> (indirectly) take care of that ?

You needed to go one level deep. The same page has gnumed-client-de which is a binary
package of this source package. On checking the same at

        https://packages.debian.org/sid/gnumed-client-de

You'd see:

        * dep: libchipcard-tools
        tools for accessing chipcards

Hence, gnumed-client is indeed threatended by the removal of libchipcard-tools.

> So, is the above irrelevant because libchipcard-tools will
> (indirectly) take care of that ?

libchipcard and libgwenhywfar both need to take care of their
individual RC bugs, yes. Nothing to be done from gnumed-client side AFAICS.

Best,
Nilesh
